<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="395" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,350,666]" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,530,556]" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Distribution.</emphasis>
Eastern half of North Caucasus, mountains of Southern 
<collectingCountry box="[973,1104,531,557]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
and Central Asia, South Siberia eastwards to Tyva, 
<collectingCountry box="[403,516,567,593]" name="Mongolia" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
. In Southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[708,839,567,593]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
was found only on Dzhungarsky Alatau Range.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
